## Directory Structure

```
src/
  features/       # Domain-driven modules — main business logic lives here
  components/     # Shared components (UI atoms, layouts, AI elements)
  hooks/          # Shared hooks
  stores/         # Zustand stores (UI/client state only)
  lib/            # queryClient, i18n, sentry, env, utils
  integrations/supabase/  # client.ts + generated types.ts
  contexts/       # React contexts (Auth, AI, Language, Analytics)
  services/       # Business services (stripe, logger, analytics, etc.)
  pages/          # Public/marketing pages (thin wrappers)
  types/          # Shared TypeScript interfaces
supabase/
  functions/      # Deno Edge Functions
  migrations/     # SQL migrations
```

## Feature Modules (`src/features/`)

Each feature has `pages/`, `components/`, `hooks/`, and `api/` subdirectories.

| Feature | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| `admin` | Admin panel — users, subscriptions, logs, config |
| `ai` | AI chat canvas, Khaos Agent |
| `assistant-portal` | Assistant upgrade flow, shadow accounts |
| `assistants` | Professional's team management |
| `auth` | Login, register, MFA, password reset |
| `calendar` | Event calendar + Google Calendar sync |
| `clients` | Client (wedding client) management |
| `contracts` | Contract editor, e-signature, PDF |
| `dashboard` | Main dashboard with metrics |
| `financial` | Revenue, billing, transactions |
| `microsite` | Public microsite editor |
| `pipeline` | Sales pipeline / leads |
| `portal` | Client-facing bride dashboard |
| `projects` | Project/event management |
| `public-booking` | Public booking form (`/b/:slug`) |

## Auth & Roles

- `useAuth()` — access current user (from `AuthContext`)
- `useRole()` — checks `makeup_artists` and `assistants` tables
- `usePlanAccess()` — feature flags and usage limits via Supabase RPC
- `<ProtectedRoute>` — requires authenticated user
- `<AdminRoute>` — requires admin role

## Supabase

- Two environments: **dev** (`nqufpfpqtycxxqtnkkfh`) and **prod** (`pymdkngcpbmcnayxieod`)
- RLS enabled on all user-data tables
- Edge Functions are Deno/TypeScript in `supabase/functions/`
- Import client from `@/integrations/supabase/client`
